title: Genevieve
summary: Genevieve (French: Sainte Geneviève; Latin: Sancta Genovefa, Genoveva; from Gaullish geno "race, lineage" and uida "sage";[1] c. 419/422 AD – 502/512 AD) is the patroness saint of Paris in the Roman Catholic and Eastern Orthodox traditions. Her feast day is kept on 3 January.
